Tîrnova is a commune in Dondușeni District, Moldova. It is composed of three villages: Briceva, Elenovca (formerly Elena-Doamnă) and Tîrnova.Briceva (also Brichevo, Bricheva, Yiddish: בריטשעווע, romanized: Britcheva) was established as a Jewish agricultural colony in 1836 and maintained Jewish majority until World War II.

